  "customHelp": "=== FIRST-GAME SETUP === (1) Open the Decks menu and load a Starter deck (Humans / Savages / Living Earth / Regals). (2) Your ADAPTATION DECK (the 7 Adaptation cards you built) starts FACE DOWN in its own pile (bottom-left) automatically — separate from your main deck, never shuffled in or drawn to hand. (3) Your Treachery counter starts at 5. You need a 2nd player on the same game link (custom games have no public matchmaking) — or play both sides solo to learn. Arena does NOT enforce rules; you run the turn yourselves. === HOW TO PLAY === Green = Harvester (gather energy). Red = Reaper (hunt). When you PLAY a Reaper or Harvester it enters your HOME zone. A creature can't push into TO INVADE (the opponent's area) until your NEXT turn (no invading the turn it's played). COUNTERS in order: Energy | Balance | Treachery. ENERGY = your spendable pool this turn (Raw + Life merged into one to cut clicks) — gain it at Dawn, spend it, convert leftover to Population at Dusk. BALANCE = your score. TREACHERY = how HARD YOUR LAND IS TO INVADE (1-10, STARTS AT 5). High = fortified; low = wide open, so you want YOURS high and your opponent's low. Greedy energy (e.g. Overdraw Rig) lowers your own treachery. ADAPTATIONS = your energy sites (formerly called Creators — same thing, one name now). You BUILD a 7-card Adaptation Deck in the deckbuilder (Adaptation category, multiples allowed) — at game start it routes to its OWN face-down pile at bottom-left. At DAWN, play the top one: it flips face up and lands in your ADAPTATIONS zone automatically. SUN glyph = FREE; CRESCENT MOON glyph = goes to your HAND instead, pay its cost to play it at DUSK. The Adaptations zone is your energy base. POPULATION = red pips placed on your Harvesters (this is what accumulates). Tokens: red pip = Population, black = Death.",
